SIMPLE: obscenity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obscenity
<hw>Ob*scen"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Obscenities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>obscentias</ets>: cf. F. <ets>obsc⟦eacute⟧nit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>That quality in words or things which presents what is offensive to
chastity or purity of mind; obscene or impure language or acts; moral
impurity; lewdness; obsceneness; <as>as, the <ex>obscenity</ex> of a
speech, or a picture</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mr. Cowley asserts plainly, that <qex>obscenity</qex> has no place
in wit.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No pardon vile <qex>obscenity</qex> should find.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obscurant</ent>⟦br⟧
